The paper deals with a combinatorial problem on graphs, specifically the Independent Set Reconfiguration problem. This problem is related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the parameterization of the problem by modular-width, which is a structural parameter of graphs. This connects the paper to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories, which deal with the analysis of algorithms and computational problems on graphs. Finally, the paper mentions that the problem is well-studied and has been previously studied under different rules, which suggests a connection to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category, which deals with the intersection of computer science and game theory.
